<br>
We were avenged by a fair wizardess and her companion who saw our demise, to this I am greatful. And to the members of Dreadstorm and their ilk, this is not finished, we will have our day yet..<br>
<br>
/occ: all in all i had a good time even if there was mass confusion in the end. I was hoping to get some dead from LoS but Dreadstorm fit the bill quite nicely. Kudo's to those who attended. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udaliondveldrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalion DVeldrin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/24/02 8:02:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The battle of the Arena</span><hr size=1> ((ooc))<br>
